The paper deals with the representation learning of neural network agents, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of generative models and supervised learning also suggests a focus on neural networks and their optimization, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). The case study of pole-balancing involves control systems and robotics, which could be classified under systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the use of embeddings is a common technique in computer vision (cs.CV), although it is not the main focus of the paper.
